WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
[Amit Varma]: This episode of The Seen and The Unseen is brought to you by Intel.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.000
[Amit Varma]: There is this old cartoon that I remember from time to time.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:17.000
[Amit Varma]: It features two wolves and a lamb arguing about what to have for dinner.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.000
[Amit Varma]: Guess what the wolves want?

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.000
[Amit Varma]: When they can't reach a consensus for which lamb would agree to be eaten,

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:24.000
[Amit Varma]: one of the wolves says,

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
[Amit Varma]: let's vote and go by what the majority wants.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:29.000
[Amit Varma]: Remember, two wolves, one lamb.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:34.000
[Amit Varma]: And this is why a democracy needs to be about much more than just voting.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.000
[Amit Varma]: You need to have a vote, but you need to protect the lamb.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.000
[Amit Varma]: In theory, our constitution does this.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:45.000
[Amit Varma]: Though my constant lament is that it protects the state from the individual more than the other way around.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.000
[Amit Varma]: In theory also, our institutions and processes do this.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:53.000
[Amit Varma]: Our parliament, after all, is there to help keep a check on the government in power,

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
[Amit Varma]: to keep it accountable, to help it do its job well.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
[Amit Varma]: But is it like that in practice?

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:03.000
[Amit Varma]: I'm pessimistic about some of these questions, but my guest today is an optimist.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:08.000
[Amit Varma]: More than that, while I am an armchair pessimist, he is an on-the-ground optimist.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:13.000
[Amit Varma]: He gets up in the morning every day looking forward to how he can make our democracy function better.

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:34.000
[Unknown]: And I think I might become a bit of an optimist myself because of people like M.R. Madhavan.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.000
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to The Scene and The Unseen.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:41.000
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is M.R. Madhavan, who left a thriving corporate career a decade and a half ago

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:48.000
[Amit Varma]: to set up PRS Legislative Research which aims to make our legislators better informed about issues that face India.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.000
[Amit Varma]: If you think about it, this was a gap in the market.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:55.000
[Amit Varma]: Our legislators come to parliament after they have become experts in the art of winning elections.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:59.000
[Amit Varma]: But for no fault of their own, they may not know much about governance

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:03.000
[Amit Varma]: or the complex policy issues that they suddenly have to vote on.

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:08.000
[Amit Varma]: Madhavan and his PRS co-founder C.V. Madhukar decided to fill this gap

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:14.000
[Amit Varma]: by creating research that would educate parliamentarians and help them make good decisions.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:19.000
[Amit Varma]: To their delight, they found that there was a market for this and many parliamentarians wanted to learn.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:23.000
[Amit Varma]: Since they started in 2005, they have also come up with other initiatives

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:26.000
[Amit Varma]: such as the LAMP Fellowship that strengthen our democracy.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:29.000
[Amit Varma]: I was delighted when Madhavan agreed to join me on the show

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:32.000
[Amit Varma]: and I wanted to pick his brains on subjects that I have been thinking about

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:35.000
[Amit Varma]: and exploring on this podcast for a long, long time.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:38.000
[Amit Varma]: I love this conversation and I hope you do as well.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:03:05.000
[Amit Varma]: Before we get there though, let's take a quick commercial break.

